Low-Pass Filter¶

I choose 3x3 simple array and apply to every pixel with taking mean mul of neigbors which collapse with my kernel array.

In [59]:
from scipy.signal import convolve2d as conv2
# same options just apply 3x3 kernel array to all the fit pixels and others will be zero
# so we will see a black border in image

Salt and pepper image¶

Add some salt and pepper to image

I will use median of neighbours pixels value so we can clean salt and pepper on it.

In [85]:
def saltPepper(img_array, ratio=0.02):
    count = int(img_array.size * ratio)
    for i in range(count):
        img_array[np.random.randint(0,255,dtype=np.uint8)][np.random.randint(0,255,dtype=np.uint8)] = [255] if i%2 == 0 else [0]
In [86]:
saltPepper(array)
